	Month = {JUL 7},
	Abstract = {Information about an individual's place and date of birth can be
	exploited to predict his or her Social Security number (SSN). Using only
	publicly available information, we observed a correlation between
	individuals' SSNs and their birth data and found that for younger
	cohorts the correlation allows statistical inference of private SSNs.
