	Abstract = {Communication technology is challenging traditional self-presentation
	strategies and behavior. Deliberate image construction is becoming more
	difficult because of the increasing number of information sources about
	individuals online. The present study examines a range of
	self-presentation behaviors on social network sites (SNS) by drawing on
	impression motivation, contingencies of self-worth, and the analysis of
	social network structure. Results from the survey data show that users
