	Pages = {465-491},
	Month = {SEP},
	Abstract = {Are voluntary associations integrative forces in our society because
	they promote diverse social ties, or do they primarily promote ties
	between socially similar people? The answer depends on the location and
	type of the organization. Neighborhood organizations reinforce network
	density and homogeneity, whereas more distant organizations enhance
	network diversity. In contrast to instrumental organizations, expressive
	organizations increase network density and homogeneity. When
