	Volume = {101},
	Number = {5},
	Pages = {763-776},
	Month = {DEC},
	Abstract = {I study a dyadic linking model in which agents form directed links that
	exhibit homophily and reciprocity. A fixed-effect approach accounts for
	unobserved sources of degree heterogeneity. I consider specification
	testing and inference with respect to the homophily and reciprocity
	parameters. The specification test compares observed transitivity to
	predicted transitivity. All test statistics account for the presence of
