	Pages = {120-147},
	Month = {APR 3},
	Abstract = {In this paper, we analyze data on the opinion dynamics of 1,660,927
	users of an online social network using formal models of opinion
	formation. We have observed that moderate users have a tendency to
	follow the average opinion of their online friends, which we interpret
	as a presence of bounded confidence. Further, we have discovered that
