	Volume = {48},
	Number = {3},
	Pages = {1325-1336},
	Month = {MAY},
	Abstract = {Most of current social network services are vulnerable to malicious
	actions. For example, rumor (e.g., contaminated and distorted
	information) can be diffused along the social links. In this paper,
	given a social network service, we design a peer-to-peer (P2P) network,
	and propose a robust information diffusion model to efficiently detect
	the malicious peers from which a risk (i.e., rumor) has been generated
	on the P2P network. Thereby, by aggregating social interactions among
	users, a set of interaction sequences are obtained. Given a set of
	interaction sequences, statistical sequence mining method is exploited
	to discover a certain social position which provides peculiar patterns
