	Number = {11},
	Pages = {1864-1878},
	Month = {JUL},
	Abstract = {Two sets of survey data from East and West Germany in 1988 to 1990 and
	in 1996 containing information about the structure of ego-centered
	networks of parents living together with at least one child, are used to
	rest empirically whether the structure of the social networks have
	changed during the transformation period. Contrary to what is commonly
	believed by the East German population and what is a main theme in the
