	Volume = {37},
	Number = {3},
	Pages = {159-191},
	Month = {JUL 1},
	Abstract = {Although both betweenness and closeness centrality are claimed to be
	important for the effectiveness of someone's network position, it has
	not been comprehensively studied which networks emerge if actors strive
	to optimize their centrality in the network in terms of betweenness and
	closeness. We study each of these centrality measures separately, but we
	also analyze what happens if actors value betweenness and closeness
	simultaneously. Network dynamics differ considerably in a scenario with
	either betweenness or closeness incentives compared with a scenario in
	which closeness and betweenness incentives are combined. There are not
	only more stable networks if actors' betweenness and closeness are
