	Number = {3},
	Pages = {251-272},
	Month = {JUL},
	Abstract = {Previously, theories of network exchange and their applications focused
	only on static configurations. The purpose of this paper is to show that
	exchange networks with dynamic structures can be analyzed using Network
	Exchange Theory (NET) even though that theory was developed with only
	static networks in mind. The Exchange Seek Likelihood (ESL) and
	Optimal-Seek methods of NET are used. Hypotheses, which focus on network
