	Month = {OCT},
	Abstract = {Cryptocurrencies have embraced Twitter as a major channel of
	communication. Employing social network analysis and sentiment analysis,
	this study investigates the Twitter-mediated communication behaviors
	among cryptocurrencies. This study determines whether a significant
	association exists between cryptocurrencies' Twitter networks and their
	credit scores. Data were drawn from the Twitter pages of several top
	cryptocurrencies. The results indicate that reply-mention networks had
	the densest structure, that the following-follower network structure was
	correlated with the reply-mention structure, and that the reply-mention
