	proposition that virtual organizations can more effectively create and
	leverage knowledge due to diverse information, skills, and resources to
	enhance capacity to innovate. Yet, relatively little is known about
	desirable organizing processes in virtual open science communities. To
	this end, a simulation-based exploratory study is conducted to better
